In a #saucepan{}, make a simple syrup with the @sugar{1.75%cups} and 1 cup of @water{1%cup}. Bring to a boil and stir to make sure the sugar is dissolved. Allow syrup to cool, then cover and place in refrigerator until well chilled.

In a #pitcher{}, stir together simple syrup, @lemon juice{1.5%cups} with pulp (make sure all seeds are removed!) and remaining 7 cups of @water{7%cup}.

Enjoy over ice on a hot day. [- For a "spiked" version substitute 2 cups of the water with 1.5 to 1.75 cups of vodka -]
